cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to improve procedural text comprehension. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of learning frameworks and models, which suggests that it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of consistency bias, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a standard benchmark dataset, which could also place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
